Payroll

Class Company

  • java.lang.Object
    • Payroll.Company

  • public class Company
extends java.lang.Object
    Creates a new Company instance, an array of employees. Array of employees will automatically grow when maximum capacity is reached, methods allow the addition/removal of employees from the class, as well as several different methods of printing all employees in the array.
    Author:
    Craig Li, Prerak Patel

        public int getNumEmployees()
        Gets number of employees.
        Returns:

      • find

        private int find(Employee employee)
        Searches employee list to find index of an employee.
        Parameters:
        employee - the employee you want to find
        Returns:
        index int value representing index where employee is located. Will have value of -1 (FAILCONDITION) if employee is not found.

      • grow

        private void grow()
        Increases capacity of employee list by GROWAMOUNT (4) by creating a larger array, and copying values of the original array over.

      • add

        public boolean add(Employee employee)
        Adds an employee to the employee list array. Checks array if employee is already in list, and will grow employee list if at maximum capacity.
        Parameters:
        employee - employee object to be added to the employee list
        Returns:
        false if employee is already in array, true if employee is not in array and is successfully added.

      • remove

        public boolean remove(Employee employee)
        Removes an employee from the employee list.
        Parameters:
        employee - employee to be removed from the list.
        Returns:
        returns true if employee is successfully located and removed, false if the employee is not found.

      • setHours

        public boolean setHours(Employee employee)

        Parameters:
        employee - employee that requires hours to be set.
        Returns:
        true if employee's hours are changed, false if not a parttime employee, or employee does not exist in employee list.

      • deptCheck

        private boolean deptCheck(Employee first,
                          Employee second)
        Checks if an employee (first) has a department that comes lexicographically before another employee's (second).
        Parameters:
        first - original employee to compare departments against
        second - comparator employee against first.
        Returns:
        true if the first employee's department is before the second employee's department, false if not.

      • isOlder

        private boolean isOlder(Employee first,
                        Employee second)
        Helper method that compares the hire dates of two employees.
        Parameters:
        first - iterative employee being compared to current oldest employee.
        second - current oldest employee found so far in array.
        Returns:
        true true if first is older than second, false otherwise.
